Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.92,0:00:06.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Star" is a fascinating word.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.42,0:00:07.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can refer to both culprits and actors!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.88,0:00:09.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sight, hearing and smell...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.71,0:00:11.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All of their alibis relied on these three senses.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.26,0:00:12.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The hint that breaks them apart lies in a past case!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.88,0:00:14.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seeing through to the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.51,0:00:16.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I look like a child, but have the intellect of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.26,0:00:18.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.21,0:00:23.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, we felt the same light the moment we met.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.10,0:00:29.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, lots and lots of the same emotions filled our eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.85,0:00:35.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although the signals you sent destroyed my theory...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.75,0:00:41.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These feelings were always beyond your reach
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.74,0:00:47.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, let's fight, go against our morals...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.78,0:00:52.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And aim for a wider world!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.30,0:00:59.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, glimmering star, shine over us forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.15,0:01:05.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way, we won't lose the dreams we had when we were young...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.13,0:01:11.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't care if this town{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ges someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.10,0:01:17.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only thing I don't want to{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ge is you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.20,0:01:23.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, glimmering star, shine over us forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.90,0:01:29.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way, we won't lose the dreams we had when we were young...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.00,0:01:39.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,1350)}The only thing I don't want to{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ge is you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.85,0:01:44.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Strange Family's Request:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.81,0:01:45.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Part 2!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.48,0:01:50.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the suspects are...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.50,0:01:53.79,CharCards01 bord,,0,0,0,,{\fade(500,0)}Kariya Daisaku (68)\N{\fs16.5}Master of the Household
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.56,0:01:53.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The master of the house, who was confined to his\Nroom while playing a wooden flute: Daisaku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.10,0:01:56.79,CharCards02 bord,,0,0,0,,{\fade(500,0)}Kariya Tsugutaka (42)\N{\fs11}\h\hEldest Son of the Kariya Household\h\h
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.11,0:01:56.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The eldest son who was drawing an\Nillustration in his room: Tsugutaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.10,0:01:59.92,CharCards03 bord,,0,0,0,,{\fade(500,300)}Kariya Shigehide (37)\N{\fs11}\hSecond Son of the Kariya Household\h
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.86,0:02:00.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the second son, who was\Nwriting a novel: Shigehide{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.41,0:02:02.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just those three.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.95,0:02:04.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.08,0:02:07.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All the deductions made up to this\Npoint stemmed from Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s guidance.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.87,0:02:10.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By saying things that would\Nordinarily be pointed out by a child...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.46,0:02:13.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's making it seem like the\NHints he leaves are just coincidences.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.38,0:02:18.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, even he would be able to do that if\Nhe was getting Shinichi's deductions secretly...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.34,0:02:23.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he didn't make any calls when\Nhe came across something just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.39,0:02:26.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, I can only think of one other possible explanation...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.81,0:02:27.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This child is...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.87,0:02:31.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} is actually...{\t(2430,2431,} Shinichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.06,0:02:36.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's why the calls I get from Shinichi\Nare always listed as an anonymous number!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.53,0:02:39.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's so I can't call him!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.03,0:02:42.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But they were both together during the school festival...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.91,0:02:44.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Am I overthinking things after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.29,0:02:48.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I can't fall for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.00,0:02:49.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is Shinichi, I'm talking about!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.37,0:02:51.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He must have used some kind of trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.12,0:02:53.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Ran-neechan?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.29,0:02:54.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.59,0:02:56.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-Ah, I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.34,0:02:58.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've got to make sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.21,0:03:01.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, just after I sent that e-mail to Shinichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.34,0:03:03.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s cell phone rang.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.43,0:03:06.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll send that mail one more time...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.81,0:03:08.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Arid I'll catch you this time for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.14,0:03:10.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This time, you definitely won't be able to weasel out of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.94,0:03:12.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because I'll have the perfect evidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.07,0:03:18.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.36,0:03:20.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not ringing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.86,0:03:23.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A guest?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.11,0:03:24.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were you expecting someone to be coming by?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.50,0:03:26.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.12,0:03:30.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It says my message was re-sent, so was\Nwhat happened this morning just a coincidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.12,0:03:33.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course it was. Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} couldn't be Shinichi, could he?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.83,0:03:36.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I'm up against that conniving Shinichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.54,0:03:40.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He might be using some kind of method\Nthat a regular person like me wouldn't consider.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.34,0:03:42.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're going to play this game with me...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.13,0:03:46.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then I'm not letting you out of my sight one second until\Nyou slip up and do something that reveals your identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.05,0:03:48.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You better prepare yourself, Shinichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.23,0:03:51.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? Is this another one of those pranks?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.85,0:03:53.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? A prank?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.52,0:03:56.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are times when the doorbell rings, but nobody's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.36,0:03:59.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's especially terrible today,\Nwhat with all the times it's been rung.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.65,0:04:01.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It normally only happens a couple of times a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.86,0:04:05.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A child playing a prank at this time of night?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.62,0:04:10.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems to me that someone among those three\Nfound a way to ring the doorbell from their room...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.16,0:04:13.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And built their alibi during the time\Nthe housekeepers went to the entryway.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.37,0:04:15.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true that their three alibis...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.50,0:04:18.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rely on these women stating\Nthat the three were in their rooms...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.29,0:04:21.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When they placed dinner in front of\Ntheir doors at 7:30 PM, the time of the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.42,0:04:24.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, they never saw them face to face.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.26,0:04:30.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, the most suspicious is the\Nlate Tomoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s husband, Tsugutaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.18,0:04:35.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we assume he saw the e-mails about her affair\Nthat were stored in her cell phone, we have his motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.94,0:04:38.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, if anyone knew the mistress was having an affair...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.65,0:04:41.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think the master would have kept quiet about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.94,0:04:43.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why do you think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.53,0:04:50.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Motoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the fiancée of their third son, Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r},\Nwas found murdered in a phone booth 12 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.33,0:04:52.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She had actually been in the middle of a date with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.45,0:04:54.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At first, Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} called...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.33,0:04:59.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Asking if Motoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} could sleep at our\Nhouse, since she had missed the last train.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.00,0:05:03.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The master, who was in the living room\Nat the time, told me to let him speak to Motoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.51,0:05:09.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Keep in mind that if a filthy woman like you becomes\Na member of our Kariya family, you'll lose your life!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.97,0:05:12.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Motoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was unfaithful?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.47,0:05:16.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We don't know where the master got that information...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.44,0:05:20.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But while she and Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} were stuck\Nthere with no place to go, they were assaulted.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.98,0:05:22.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you inform the police of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.36,0:05:25.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We only told them about the call.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.40,0:05:29.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since it was not related to the incident, the second son,\NShigehide{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} told us to keep quiet about the affair.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.16,0:05:35.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the only one who wouldn't have a motive\Nto kill Tomoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} would be Shigehide{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.08,0:05:36.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About that...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.96,0:05:42.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I actually heard Madam Tomoko and\NShigehide{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} quarreling in the corridor a month ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.63,0:05:44.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She said "How rotten of you to eavesdrop on me!"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.88,0:05:48.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter what, it was always about the main character's\Nparents in the novel that's being adapted into a TV drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.78,0:05:51.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was saying that their conversation in the\Ndrama was just lifted from her own conversation...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.77,0:05:55.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So Madam Tomoko stated that she would sue him if he\Ndoesn't{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ge the lines before the drama was completed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.68,0:05:56.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was really threatening.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.89,0:06:02.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the end, Shigehide{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}\Nkindly agreed to{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ge the dialogue.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.27,0:06:05.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's you? ls there something else?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.69,0:06:07.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you find the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.49,0:06:08.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.53,0:06:13.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, when your dinner\Nwas brought here at 7:30 PM...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.12,0:06:17.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were told that you said "We're having curry-rice today,\Nhuh? Haven't had that for a while!" through the paper door.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.25,0:06:19.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did you know it was curry?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.71,0:06:23.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The smell. The paper door was slightly open.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.04,0:06:25.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, what are you using this for?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.21,0:06:26.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.51,0:06:31.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I use it to listen to my flute teacher's\Nperformance as a model to practice from everyday.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.64,0:06:36.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't go outside, so my wooden flute is\Nthe only way I can keep myself entertained.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.64,0:06:41.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He never leaves the house since he hurt his leg at work?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.27,0:06:45.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, and because he spends the entire day at home...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.07,0:06:50.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He found out his wife was having an affair, so they divorced.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.11,0:06:54.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. That's why he was much\Nstricter about infidelity than most people.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.99,0:06:59.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Curry-rice was his wife's specialty.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.12,0:07:01.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that's why you don't make it very often?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.54,0:07:03.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're minding the master's feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.65,0:07:07.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. Tonight's meal was originally going to be beef stew...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.36,0:07:09.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But ten minutes before we were about to\Nserve it, we were suddenly asked to make curry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.76,0:07:12.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on! Can you give me a break already?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.55,0:07:16.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't I already tell you that I was in this room at 7:30 PM?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.01,0:07:19.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You only moved your hand to show your\Nthanks when your"meal was brought here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.93,0:07:24.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So she didn't see you directly; she only\Nsaw your shadow through the paper door.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.52,0:07:27.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you implying that I used some kind of\Ntrick to project my shadow on the paper door?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.90,0:07:28.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.53,0:07:30.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think that's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.86,0:07:32.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, I'm pretty sure l can\Ntell if it's a person's shadow or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.74,0:07:33.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.66,0:07:36.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So if you have nothing else to ask, get out!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.62,0:07:42.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ever since you police came to this house, I haven't been able\Nto concentrate and haven't finished writing a single line!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.08,0:07:46.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A relative just passed away,\Nand he's not shedding a single tear...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.67,0:07:50.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is he really a romance novelist?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.30,0:07:51.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It sure doesn't seem like it, does it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.63,0:07:55.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of which, didn't you say\Nsomething like that when you first met him?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.64,0:07:57.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ran?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.01,0:07:58.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? W-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.06,0:08:02.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you say that you always thought he was older?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.06,0:08:06.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah... That's because Shigehide{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} rarely\Nhas people with brown-dyed hair in his novels...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.82,0:08:10.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And even when he does, it always seems to\Nbe a bad person with little to no significance.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.78,0:08:12.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I thought he was an elderly man.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.74,0:08:16.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, when the main characters make it to\Nthe place where they are to meet each other...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.74,0:08:19.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They lean against a pillar and still can't see each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.24,0:08:21.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's like a scene in an old movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.29,0:08:26.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They rarely get to meet, so their feelings are\Nvery melancholic as they worry about each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.79,0:08:32.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's completely different from a certain someone\Nwho's living with his companion, secretly looking over her!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.84,0:08:36.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}? Don't you think so, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.43,0:08:39.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-I'm a kid, so I don't really understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.10,0:08:41.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You think so too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.10,0:08:41.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.56,0:08:44.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You sure are exasperating.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.44,0:08:47.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've been here the whole time,\Nso I can't tell you anything new.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.90,0:08:52.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, the scent of the pipe that was\Nfloating in the air when your meal was brought here...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.19,0:08:54.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can't be considered valid proof of your alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.20,0:08:56.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So whose pipe could that have been?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.16,0:08:57.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying there's a double of me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.66,0:08:59.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A double?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.29,0:09:01.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You ate your curry?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.95,0:09:02.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.20,0:09:05.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,More importantly, did someone else show up again?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.25,0:09:06.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The doorbell was ringing earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.79,0:09:10.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No. It seems it was another prank.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.76,0:09:16.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These pranks have been making Tsugutaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} very angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.01,0:09:18.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For example, when he's comes back from a outing...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.76,0:09:21.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He always asks, "Did another one\Nof those pranks happen again today?"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.26,0:09:24.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we answer yes, he bursts into rage.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.27,0:09:28.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, and he also became angry over those phone pranks.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.56,0:09:29.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.23,0:09:31.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. It's a bunch of weird calls\Nwhere they ring once, and then hang up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.65,0:09:35.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then they wait a while, ring, and then hang up again!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.11,0:09:38.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was also one around 8:00 today,\Nshortly before you police arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.91,0:09:40.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are they anonymous calls?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.37,0:09:44.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No. But even though a call came in,\Nthere's nothing in the call history!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.91,0:09:46.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me that the doorbell earlier was actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.79,0:09:48.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ran-neechan!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.58,0:09:49.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.09,0:09:51.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You sent a e-mail earlier, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.63,0:09:52.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.05,0:09:53.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You sent one, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.38,0:09:56.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I did. Something wrong with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.30,0:09:59.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you make sure to check the e-mail address?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.72,0:10:03.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't need to check it if I'm only\Nre-sending a mail I sent this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.27,0:10:07.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? Whose e-mail address is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.02,0:10:08.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.90,0:10:11.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why she was able to find her cell phone so easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.86,0:10:13.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.02,0:10:15.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit is that person!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.03,0:10:19.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They hid in the dark shadows from 12\Nyears ago, and used them to their advantage...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.66,0:10:23.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to make themselves be\Nthe only one remaining in the light!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.21,0:10:31.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, how about we stop for today?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.71,0:10:33.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.00,0:10:36.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, it doesn't seem like their alibis can\Nbe disproved unless they used a magic trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.84,0:10:38.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A magic trick?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.26,0:10:42.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that reminds me! I saw a really\Nneat magic trick on TV the other day!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.30,0:10:42.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.68,0:10:45.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a young lady in a vertical box...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.52,0:10:49.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who had her face, hands, and feet sticking out, even\Nthough the box was separated into three different parts!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.14,0:10:50.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was really surprised!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.90,0:10:54.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You idiot! There were three people in the box!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.44,0:10:56.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I get it...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.23,0:10:59.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if something's impossible by yourself, you can\Ntrick people like that when you work together with others!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.82,0:11:02.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, what's your point...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.12,0:11:03.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.70,0:11:07.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the three of them joined forces, they\Ncould have created a trick for their alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.87,0:11:09.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.46,0:11:13.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Their dinners were brought to them at the same time,\Nnot to mention that their rooms are pretty far apart!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.21,0:11:17.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tomoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} lost her cell phone the day before yesterday...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.88,0:11:22.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But for some reason, she found it somewhere in\Nthis house shortly before she was murdered today.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.68,0:11:26.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The three who live in this house certainly are suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.43,0:11:27.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.81,0:11:30.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Especially since we didn't find\Nher cell phone at the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.89,0:11:32.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Ran-neechan...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.48,0:11:36.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you think the person who was secretly\Ncarrying the lost cell phone was really stupid?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.48,0:11:36.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.78,0:11:39.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Remember? When we were looking for it...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.49,0:11:43.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't he answer the phone just before\Nhanging up, every time we called that number?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.70,0:11:45.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course he did!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.16,0:11:47.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we heard their voice or something,\Nwe would have figured out who they were!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.37,0:11:52.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if it was me, and I knew that\Nthose annoying calls would keep coming...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.71,0:11:55.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I would've turned off my phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.84,0:12:00.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you really did turn off your phone, Shinichi?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.34,0:12:01.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you an idiot?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.80,0:12:07.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He didn't turn the phone off because he was\Nwaiting for a message or call from his lover, Tomoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.35,0:12:11.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, couldn't he have just turned down the volume?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.06,0:12:14.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They knew the same person\Nkept calling and calling, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.48,0:12:18.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What if our perp doesn't know how to use a cell phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.48,0:12:22.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way! They managed to unlock the phone, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.40,0:12:28.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But even if it's locked, all they had to know is\Nthat they heeded to enter four digits to unlock it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.87,0:12:33.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So even if they didn't know how to use one,\Nit's still possible to unlock it if they had time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.16,0:12:37.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And everyone knows how to use a cell\Nphone after fiddling around with one for a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.09,0:12:39.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It took me a long time until I got used to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.09,0:12:43.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? But wasn't that way back when\Nyou first bought a cell phone, Inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.59,0:12:48.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, there's hardly anyone who\Ndoesn't know how to use a cell phone nowadays...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.10,0:12:52.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Except, of course, someone who has been\Nlocked up somewhere for the past 10 years or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.85,0:12:54.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,10 years?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.23,0:12:58.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it, cell phone use only\Nstarted to become widespread about 10 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.36,0:13:01.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait! Wasn't it 12 years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.28,0:13:05.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the third son, Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Ndisappeared after his fiancée was killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.53,0:13:09.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was the one\Nwho had Tomoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s cell phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.62,0:13:12.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me that he's somewhere in this house...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.62,0:13:16.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's true, then one of those\Nthree must be covering for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.75,0:13:22.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he was isolated from the outside world for\N12 years and saw a cell phone for the first time...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.21,0:13:25.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's understandable why he would be\Ninterested in it enough to take it with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.13,0:13:30.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That would explain why those calls to\NEisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s friend came from her cell phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.01,0:13:33.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And why he had enough time to disable the lock.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.81,0:13:36.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Tomoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} caught him when\Nhe was putting the cell phone back...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.98,0:13:41.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, to keep her mouth shut, he and the person\Ncovering for him came up with a plan to kill her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.82,0:13:43.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That sure would break down their alibis.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.28,0:13:46.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, go get me a warrant so we can search this house!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.20,0:13:50.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} might be the culprit of the 12-year-old case!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.16,0:13:50.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.45,0:13:54.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now the problem is how to find\Nthe one who's covering for him...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.54,0:13:56.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The master of the house, Daisaku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, is suspicious...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.96,0:13:59.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know how he had a tape recorder in his room?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.54,0:14:03.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He could have recorded himself saying, "We're having curry-rice\Ntoday, huh? Haven't had that for a while!" beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.96,0:14:08.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, when the curry was brought to him around 7:30 PM...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.76,0:14:12.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} push the play button to build his alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.89,0:14:16.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aw, this is making me get hungry!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.60,0:14:19.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, would you like some curry?\NThere's still some left over.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.69,0:14:21.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.19,0:14:25.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But didn't you originally make beef stew before\Nyou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ged it to curry 10 minutes before the meal?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.13,0:14:28.11,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Was it because it seemed like it wasn't very yummy?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.24,0:14:30.20,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Oh, no. It was nothing like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.15,0:14:30.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,10 minutes before the meal?\NThat would put it around 7:20 PM...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.32,0:14:33.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It takes over 20 minutes by car to\Nget to the crime scene from here...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.70,0:14:38.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if the crime was executed in less than 10 minutes,\Nhe still would have had to leave before 7:00 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.79,0:14:43.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, it was Tsugutaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who was drawing\Nan illustration in his room while smoking his pipe!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.88,0:14:48.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would've be easy for him to have Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} smoke\Nhis pipe enough to spread its scent around the room!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.13,0:14:51.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! But since I love curry, maybe I should have some.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.85,0:14:53.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.01,0:14:58.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You see, I love it so much that I was thinking\Nabout eating the curry in front of Mr. Illustrator's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.81,0:14:59.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, my.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.60,0:15:05.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I didn't do it since everybody would have\Nfound out right away if the plates were gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.69,0:15:07.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.07,0:15:10.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Tsugutaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} asked Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to\Nsit in his room and act as his double...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.95,0:15:13.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why didn't he take the curry in the room?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.70,0:15:15.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That would have proven he was in the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.62,0:15:18.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He must have left it out on purpose...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.33,0:15:20.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since he wasn't supposed to be out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.58,0:15:24.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if that's true, Tsugutaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} would have\Nnoticed it when he came back from the crime scene...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.71,0:15:26.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And brought it into his room with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.71,0:15:28.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if he did leave it in front of his room...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.88,0:15:33.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would only deepen our suspicion of him, since it would\Nprove that he wasn't in his room during the time of the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.09,0:15:37.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Tsugutaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} actually ate the\Ncurry later on, even though it was cold...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.72,0:15:39.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So there's no reason why he wouldn't have brought it in.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.60,0:15:45.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then it comes down to our last suspect,\NShigehide{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who's writing novels in his room...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.78,0:15:50.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm the culprit who killed Tomoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.65,0:15:52.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm covering for my little brother, Eisuke?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.57,0:15:54.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop joking around.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.74,0:15:58.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you see, everything fits with this hypothesis.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.08,0:16:02.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you asked Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to get the same hairstyle as yours...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.42,0:16:05.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something like answering with a sign\Nbehind the paper door is a simple feat.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.63,0:16:10.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.30,0:16:11.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Nishiro Tsubouchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.93,0:16:13.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm kind of tied up at the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.47,0:16:15.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'll call you back.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.05,0:16:17.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're mean, Mister.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.81,0:16:18.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.26,0:16:23.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See? Even though you use a cell phone yourself,\Nnone of the characters in your novels have one!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.98,0:16:26.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why wouldn't they have one?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.65,0:16:29.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no way you couldn't know\Nabout the existence of cell phones, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.98,0:16:31.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D-Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.03,0:16:33.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You make your younger brother write the novels?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.07,0:16:36.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's why not not many of your\Ncharacters have their hair dyed brown!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.45,0:16:39.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was still quite rare to see that 12 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.79,0:16:44.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that means that you really did use a conversation\Nbetween Tomoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and her husband in your novel!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.79,0:16:49.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If there was someone living in the attic of this house,\Nthey could hear every conversation that takes place!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.01,0:16:51.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, about that...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.17,0:16:54.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.05,0:16:56.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've done enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.10,0:16:57.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.85,0:17:00.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.18,0:17:05.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. I killed my fiancée 12 years ago\Nand my older bro's been hiding me here ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.02,0:17:06.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm Kariya Eisuke.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.10,0:17:09.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that time, when I heard what\Nmy father said over the phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.94,0:17:16.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Keep in mind that if a filthy woman like you becomes\Na member of our Kariya family, you'll lose your life!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.03,0:17:21.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We started arguing about that, and I ended\Nup stabbing Motoka in a sudden burst of rage.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.20,0:17:23.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I felt really miserable after that...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.66,0:17:27.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But when I returned home all\Ndazed, my older bro found me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.08,0:17:29.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Brother, it's horrible! I... Motoka...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.59,0:17:31.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll be fine! I'll figure something out!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.63,0:17:34.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you've been living in the attic ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.01,0:17:37.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. I often thought of going to the police\Nand turning myself in, but I wasn't brave enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.55,0:17:40.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I didn't plan on killing her!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.51,0:17:43.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So why did you hit her after you stabbed her?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.68,0:17:45.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You hit her, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.81,0:17:47.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I only stabbed her!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.85,0:17:51.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? So it was you, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.15,0:17:53.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the one who killed Motoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} 12 years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.19,0:17:56.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.32,0:17:57.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would my big bro kill Motoka?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.53,0:18:02.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps Shigehide{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was the man\NMotoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was having an affair with?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.91,0:18:04.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.70,0:18:09.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the affair took place within the family, even Daisaku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nwho doesn't leave the house, would have noticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.13,0:18:13.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. And since Tomoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} knew\Nhis secret, he shut her mouth as well...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.92,0:18:15.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By killing her with the\Nsame method he used 12 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.67,0:18:19.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everything was set up in order to\Nframe Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} with the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.80,0:18:21.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.35,0:18:24.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I mean, my brother hid me for 12 years to protect me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.68,0:18:29.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, he only protected you because he knew that he\Nwould have been exposed if you were caught by the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.69,0:18:34.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since he bludgeoned Motoka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} in\Nthe head after Eisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} stabbed her!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.53,0:18:36.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tell me he's lying, Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.99,0:18:40.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah! There's no way I'd ever do such a thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.70,0:18:43.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, didn't the lady tell us something?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.03,0:18:45.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She said the sound her cell phone\Nmakes when a call comes in got{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ged.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.50,0:18:47.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You pest! What about it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.58,0:18:49.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unless you're trying to frame me as the culprit...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.42,0:18:52.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then show me proof that I did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.88,0:18:55.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Another guest?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.05,0:18:57.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I think that's probably the sound for incoming e-mails.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.88,0:18:59.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.76,0:19:03.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Tomoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was looking for Her cell phone,\Nwasn't there one time when she went off by herself?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.43,0:19:06.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was carrying my cell phone at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.93,0:19:09.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So she must have used it to\Nsend an e-mail to her cell phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.98,0:19:12.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to look for it with this sound!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.02,0:19:14.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.32,0:19:17.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter what buttons I pushed,\NI couldn't get that sound to stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.28,0:19:20.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was panicking trying to stop it,\Nwhen Tomoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} showed up in the attic...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.07,0:19:22.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, I did manage to stop\Nthe sound for when a call comes in.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.00,0:19:29.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You made the ringtone for incoming calls\Nthe same as the Kariya's landline phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.46,0:19:31.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.17,0:19:35.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If she did that, she'd have a good pretext to drop\Nwhat she's doing and get away from the house...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.05,0:19:38.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Long enough to answer the calls or\Ne-mails from the man she was in an affair with.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.59,0:19:41.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And since that sound is ringing now...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.89,0:19:44.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It proves that somewhere in this room...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.39,0:19:50.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll find Tomoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s cell phone, which\NShigehide{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} removed from the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.98,0:19:56.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He should have just thrown it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.61,0:19:58.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He probably was afraid, and couldn't toss it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.65,0:20:02.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He must've needed to make sure she didn't\Nsay anything about how he was hiding his brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.24,0:20:06.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, we'll find out in no time, once we analyze\Nthe fingerprints and blood type on the weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.79,0:20:08.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't intend to kill her.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.00,0:20:11.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If only she hadn't said that...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.96,0:20:14.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, where do you think I found this cell phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.21,0:20:17.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the hands of your curious younger brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.38,0:20:18.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.09,0:20:21.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've been hiding him in the attic, making\Nhim spend all his free time writing novels.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.22,0:20:23.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you can take the credit, and receive\Nthe spotlight as a famous author...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.43,0:20:25.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While he spends his life in a miserable place.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.72,0:20:28.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see... I'll keep quiet, but first I'll need 10 million yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.43,0:20:31.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can take our time talking over\Nthe details somewhere more private.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.98,0:20:36.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's why you told me to keep\Nwriting while you went out that night.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.19,0:20:38.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. And the same thing happened\N12 years ago with Motoka, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.82,0:20:42.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At first, I was worried about how\Nshe was stabbed, so I came to help her.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.20,0:20:46.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was relieved to find that her injuries were minor,\Nbut just I as was about to take her to the hospital...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.07,0:20:47.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're going to take responsibility for this, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.70,0:20:49.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Responsibility? Are you talking about marriage?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.83,0:20:51.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, you freaking idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.20,0:20:53.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could we get married with that old geezer there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.58,0:20:55.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm talking about money! Money!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.63,0:21:00.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going to hound you and siphon off every\Nlast yen you have, so you better prepare yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.34,0:21:03.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.76,0:21:06.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't call me Brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.47,0:21:08.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you didn't have such a talent for writing novels...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.97,0:21:11.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I might have killed you for my advantage, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.89,0:21:13.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.44,0:21:24.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But probably didn't do that because I was the\None who wanted keep reading your novels the most.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.24,0:21:30.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In my daily life, where I could see no tomorrow...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.24,0:21:35.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm glad that I fell in love with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.92,0:21:43.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I never want these feelings to{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ge...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.72,0:21:48.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So stop time, and preserve the present that echoes throughout my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.72,0:21:54.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was once afraid to be together with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.89,0:22:01.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But although I can't{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ge others or the past...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.15,0:22:12.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ge myself and my dreams for the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.58,0:22:19.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the only one I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.88,0:22:25.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As sorrow piles up in the darkening city.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.01,0:22:33.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Forever in a soft, warm breeze...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.77,0:22:38.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We 'll be together, believing in each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.06,0:22:48.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,June Bride, I'll be with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.45,0:22:51.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They sure were a weird family!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.78,0:22:52.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As expected from of you, Uncle!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.83,0:22:54.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You solved it in the blink of an eye!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.33,0:22:55.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's just how it goes for someone like me!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.75,0:22:59.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As expected of you, Shinichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.25,0:23:01.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've mastered the skill of acting like an\Nelementary schooler who's slightly smarter than usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.92,0:23:06.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's like a large center forward that's\Nbeing controlled by a small mid-fielder...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.92,0:23:11.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fantasista who makes the perfect pass leading to a goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.92,0:23:11.59,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,{\3c&H76271F&}Note: "Fantasista" is the Italian soccer term for "striker".
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.59,0:23:13.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.26,0:23:14.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are you doing this?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.89,0:23:16.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why won't you tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.93,0:23:19.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm right next to you, and yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.60,0:23:20.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.15,0:23:24.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah... We're finally home.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.28,0:23:28.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry up and get out! I still need to return the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.07,0:23:29.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.70,0:23:34.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran, you need to hurry, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.29,0:23:37.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And make sure to heat up the bath water!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.34,0:23:49.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he really has realized!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.34,0:23:52.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's noticed that I have doubts about his true identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.01,0:23:53.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,ii fuufu\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\N11-22... A "nice couple", huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.85,0:23:55.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.43,0:23:57.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What number do you think\Nyou'd like if you had one, Shinichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.85,0:24:00.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I remember right, back then...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.48,0:24:04.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Shinichi! What on earth did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.15,0:24:05.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't remember...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.23,0:24:08.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's only one way to find out!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.15,0:24:14.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan: Ran's Suspicions.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.08,0:24:19.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.10,0:24:20.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A car's number.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.00,0:24:25.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please look forward to the next episode!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.11,0:24:22.72,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Next time, we finally make it to the 400th episode!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.75,0:24:25.32,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue Top}-kun{\r}, this is the start of a\Nnew turning point in the story, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.32,0:24:25.81,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Yep.
